gate: OPEN
task: S75-TE1
title: Verify and Fix Tracking Screen End-to-End
description: |
  Verify the complete tracking flow works against old app feature parity.

  OLD APP TRACKING FEATURES (iOS TrackerVC + Android TrackingFragment):
    - Select vehicle from list (with search)
    - Set date range: From / Until (date+time pickers)
    - Set track color (6 colors: light blue, orange, yellow, green, blue, red, purple)
    - Set track width (2px / 4px / 6px / 8px)
    - Select event types (multi-select: fuel-fill, parking, overspeed, fuel-drain)
    - Press "Build track" → show route on map with event markers
    - Playback controls: play/pause, speed, scrubber
    - Max range allowed: 7 days (show error if exceeded)

  VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:
    1. Open Tracking tab → TrackingScreen renders without error
    2. Vehicle selector opens and shows all vehicles from API
    3. From/Until date pickers work and update displayed dates
    4. "Build track" button triggers POST /ws/track/get with correct payload:
         vehicleId, fromDate (epoch ms), toDate (epoch ms), eventIds [0,9,11,12]
    5. Track renders on map (polyline visible)
    6. Event markers appear at correct positions
    7. Playback (play/pause/speed) animates the track correctly
    8. Error handling: >7 day range shows user-readable error
    9. Error handling: empty track (no GPS data) shows user-readable message
    10. Color and width selectors update the rendered track color/width

  FIX ANY FAILURES found during verification.
  Special attention to:
    - Track color: queryState.tracking.trackColor must be passed to TrackingActionScreen
    - Track width: queryState.tracking.trackWidth must be passed through
    - Event IDs: must use API codes [0, 9, 11, 12] not UI enum [1, 2, 3, 4]
      (verified fixed in sprint 63, confirm still correct)

acceptance:
  - Full tracking flow works from vehicle selection to playback
  - Track renders with selected color and width
  - Event markers appear for selected event types
  - 7-day range limit is enforced with user-visible error
  - No console errors during normal tracking flow

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 2.5 hours
